Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. records.addlTxt: No use or possession of a controlled substance or drug-related paraphernalia without a valid prescription. No use or possession of a dangerous weapon.

1:43 PM Defendant Lindsey Elaine Dahl Holm appeared by video, in custody, with Attorney Ellen Craker. Attorney Chad LaLor in court for State of Wisconsin. Court calls case. Address verified, Receives complaint, waives reading, pleads not guilty, request preliminary. Court accepts pleas.  State requests $250 cash, no use or possession of drugs or dangerous weapons. Cites no criminal history. Believes she may be homeless.
Craker argues for a signature bond. No criminal history, not FTA's. Staying at grandfather's address. No cash to post.
Court orders $3,000 signature bond, with conditions of no use or possession of drugs or paraphernalia and no use or possession of dangerous weapons.
Preliminary hearing and Arraignment scheduled for April 13, 2022 at 11:15 am.
